cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper involves the use of deep neural networks for video captioning and incorporates human gaze tracking data to improve the attention mechanism. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of movie clips and human assessment via Amazon mechanical Turk, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
